INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'd35091e6-161b-484e-8109-80d2f4b896e6',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$the_graph: Migrate from Ethers to Viem for Modern Web3 Stacks$escape$,
  $escape$When building on the_graph, you can now replace Ethers with Viem, a TypeScript-first, lightweight, and low-level library. Viem provides better performance and a more concise API. To migrate, you'll need to update your queries to use Viem's `createClient` function, which accepts the same options as `the_graph's` `graphqlClient`.

const viemClient = createClient({ url: 'https://api.thegraph.com/subgraphs/name/your-subgraph' });
const query = gql` query { ... } `;
viejClient.query({ query });

Viem's query builder is designed for complex queries, so you may need to refactor your existing queries to take advantage of its features.$escape$,
  $escape$const viemClient = createClient({ url: 'https://api.thegraph.com/subgraphs/name/your-subgraph' });
const query = gql` query { ... } `;
viejClient.query({ query });$escape$,
